WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.186 --> 00:00:04.364
Previously on Prison Break:

2
00:00:04.388 --> 00:00:05.815
I didn't kill that man. Michael.

3
00:00:05.839 --> 00:00:07.105
The evidence says you did.

4
00:00:07.174 --> 00:00:08.440
I was set up.

5
00:00:10.294 --> 00:00:11.843
<i>Put down your weapon!</i>

6
00:00:11.912 --> 00:00:14.440
I find it incumbent that you
see the inside of a prison cell.

7
00:00:14.464 --> 00:00:16.715
I'm looking for someone. A
guy named Lincoln Burrows.

8
00:00:16.783 --> 00:00:18.562
<i>Man killed the Vice
President's brother.</i>

9
00:00:18.586 --> 00:00:21.231
Why you want to see Burrows so
bad anyhow? Because he's my brother.

10
00:00:21.255 --> 00:00:22.399
I'm getting you out of here.

11
00:00:22.423 --> 00:00:23.505
It's impossible.

12
00:00:23.573 --> 00:00:25.601
Not if you designed
the place. it isn't.

13
00:00:25.625 --> 00:00:26.769
You've seen the blueprints.

14
00:00:26.793 --> 00:00:27.993
Better than that.

15
00:00:28.061 --> 00:00:29.862
I've got them on me.

16
00:00:29.930 --> 00:00:31.291
You find out who's
trying to bury him.

17
00:00:31.315 --> 00:00:32.564
Nobody's trying to bury him.

18
00:00:32.632 --> 00:00:33.999
The evidence was cooked.

19
00:00:34.068 --> 00:00:35.528
There's a lawyer poking around.

20
00:00:35.552 --> 00:00:38.002
Anyone that's a
threat is expendable.

21
00:00:40.490 --> 00:00:42.318
- I'm gonna kill that scum.
- You won't.

22
00:00:42.342 --> 00:00:44.688
You kill him. you kill our
express ticket out of here.

23
00:00:44.712 --> 00:00:46.289
What are you doing
here? Where's Maricruz?

24
00:00:46.313 --> 00:00:47.446
She's with me now.

25
00:00:47.498 --> 00:00:49.314
Fish. I gotta be back in.

26
00:00:49.383 --> 00:00:50.932
Nick Savrinn with
Project Justice.

27
00:00:51.001 --> 00:00:52.817
My boss may not
think Lincoln's case

28
00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:54.852
is worth looking into. but I do.

29
00:00:55.572 --> 00:00:56.788
When do we get started?

30
00:00:56.856 --> 00:00:58.652
Getting through this
wall is just the beginning.

31
00:00:58.676 --> 00:01:00.119
<i>There's a whole
lot of real estate</i>

32
00:01:00.143 --> 00:01:02.177
<i>in between here
and the outside walls.</i>

33
00:01:02.262 --> 00:01:03.996
That is a transfer request.

34
00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:06.815
<i>Michael Scofield is getting
shipped out tomorrow.</i>

35
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:14.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

36
00:01:39.816 --> 00:01:42.634
I assume this is about your
transfer request for Michael Scofield.

37
00:01:42.703 --> 00:01:45.103
More specifically.
why you denied it.

38
00:01:45.322 --> 00:01:46.755
Look. Mr. Kellerman.

39
00:01:46.824 --> 00:01:50.225
do I come into your house and
tell you where to put your furniture?

40
00:01:50.294 --> 00:01:52.594
We're just asking for a
professional courtesy.

41
00:01:52.663 --> 00:01:55.509
But you're asking for a federal
courtesy in a state penitentiary.

42
00:01:55.533 --> 00:01:57.515
Most people in your
position would be happy

43
00:01:57.584 --> 00:01:59.262
to have another body
taken off their hands.

44
00:01:59.286 --> 00:02:00.880
These men are my responsibility.

45
00:02:00.904 --> 00:02:02.732
From the minute they
walk through those walls

46
00:02:02.756 --> 00:02:04.934
to the time that they've
paid their debt to society.

47
00:02:04.958 --> 00:02:06.425
I'm responsible for them.

48
00:02:06.493 --> 00:02:08.120
Which means that
unless Mr. Scofield

49
00:02:08.144 --> 00:02:09.689
has done something
I don't know about.

50
00:02:09.713 --> 00:02:13.148
he is gonna stay here at
Fox River. under my watch.

51
00:02:13.217 --> 00:02:14.828
Mr. Pope. in our line of work.

52
00:02:14.852 --> 00:02:17.396
we've discovered that just about
everyone has done something

53
00:02:17.420 --> 00:02:19.540
that someone doesn't know about.

54
00:02:21.809 --> 00:02:24.526
What's this? Right now.
just a piece of history.

55
00:02:24.595 --> 00:02:26.422
Whether it becomes
a current event.

56
00:02:26.446 --> 00:02:27.979
now. that's up to you.

57
00:02:33.136 --> 00:02:36.021
My wife already
knows about Toledo.

58
00:02:36.089 --> 00:02:37.405
Does she. really?

59
00:02:44.464 --> 00:02:46.397
You're a smart man. Warden.

60
00:02:46.466 --> 00:02:48.678
I'm sure if you look hard
enough. you can find a reason

61
00:02:48.702 --> 00:02:50.969
why Michael Scofield's
presence is no longer required

62
00:02:51.038 --> 00:02:53.278
at this particular
correctional facility.

63
00:03:06.637 --> 00:03:08.517
I need some more PVC here. boss.

64
00:03:21.769 --> 00:03:23.935
Boss? Sure thing. Burrows.

65
00:03:23.987 --> 00:03:26.572
But. hey. I'm gonna check
your trunk for splinters.

66
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:27.850
I want every piece
accounted for.

67
00:03:27.874 --> 00:03:28.923
Sure.

68
00:03:30.144 --> 00:03:32.794
I got a ripped
fertilizer bag inside.

69
00:03:35.432 --> 00:03:36.664
Hey. you.

70
00:03:37.417 --> 00:03:38.650
You.

71
00:03:39.586 --> 00:03:41.019
Get in there and clean it up

72
00:03:41.088 --> 00:03:44.008
before this whole place
starts smelling like San Juan.

73
00:03:47.744 --> 00:03:49.143
Okay. he's on his way.

74
00:03:49.212 --> 00:03:51.572
Do you mind telling me
what this is all about?

75
00:03:55.769 --> 00:03:57.929
These are the guys
we're breaking out with.

76
00:03:58.872 --> 00:04:00.722
I don't think so. Fish.

77
00:04:00.791 --> 00:04:02.623
That was not our agreement.

78
00:04:03.744 --> 00:04:06.828
I'm not gonna work
with this crazy rhino.

79
00:04:06.897 --> 00:04:08.057
Keep pushing it. John.

80
00:04:08.081 --> 00:04:10.548
Yeah. I keep pushing
it. you know. Huh?

81
00:04:10.617 --> 00:04:12.684
What's your deal. man?

82
00:04:12.753 --> 00:04:14.869
Touch my brother
again. I'll show you.

83
00:04:19.376 --> 00:04:22.226
Brother? Your brother?

84
00:04:26.333 --> 00:04:28.166
We've only got a few minutes.

85
00:04:28.234 --> 00:04:30.146
Are we gonna spend
them spitting on each other.

86
00:04:30.170 --> 00:04:32.053
or are we gonna
talk some business?

87
00:04:32.122 --> 00:04:35.290
The reason we're all here today
is we have a decision to make.

88
00:04:35.359 --> 00:04:36.742
Yeah? English.

89
00:04:36.810 --> 00:04:38.377
Fitz or Percy.

90
00:04:38.445 --> 00:04:41.429
If we're gonna pull this off. we
need to take one of them out.

91
00:04:43.466 --> 00:04:46.251
And you want us to
tell you which one?

92
00:04:46.320 --> 00:04:48.386
I just want you to
help me get to them.

93
00:04:48.438 --> 00:04:49.737
I'll take it from there.

94
00:04:49.823 --> 00:04:50.934
You're crazy. you know that?

95
00:04:50.958 --> 00:04:52.067
All I need is five minutes.

96
00:04:52.091 --> 00:04:53.937
Oh. you won't even
get five seconds.

97
00:04:53.961 --> 00:04:55.977
Thought you had
everything worked out. Fish.

98
00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:58.596
We're not breaking out of
a Jamba Juice. gentlemen.

99
00:04:58.665 --> 00:05:00.932
It's gonna take a little more
than digging a few holes.

100
00:05:01.001 --> 00:05:02.417
There are eyes. ears.

101
00:05:02.485 --> 00:05:05.069
dots that couldn't be
connected from the outside.

102
00:05:05.138 --> 00:05:06.972
And English. Fitz and Percy?

103
00:05:07.041 --> 00:05:08.740
One of those dots.

104
00:05:11.211 --> 00:05:15.596
And how exactly are you
supposed to pull this off?

105
00:05:15.665 --> 00:05:17.915
With a little help
from my friends.

106
00:05:35.385 --> 00:05:38.403
Sucre. hold up. Scofield.
you got company.

107
00:05:48.531 --> 00:05:50.632
Why do I get the feeling
that there's more to you

108
00:05:50.701 --> 00:05:52.221
than meets the eye. Scofield?

109
00:05:54.971 --> 00:05:56.521
Anything you wanna tell me?

110
00:05:59.843 --> 00:06:01.343
Some other reason you're in here

111
00:06:01.428 --> 00:06:03.728
besides holding up a bank?

112
00:06:15.809 --> 00:06:17.609
You're being transferred.

113
00:06:17.678 --> 00:06:18.777
What?

114
00:06:18.829 --> 00:06:20.749
We're moving you
over to Statesville.

115
00:06:21.465 --> 00:06:22.665
You can't do that.

116
00:06:22.699 --> 00:06:24.716
Yes. I can. I'm the boss here.

117
00:06:24.785 --> 00:06:26.118
This is my house.

118
00:06:28.104 --> 00:06:30.305
Three weeks. What for?

119
00:06:30.374 --> 00:06:32.256
Lincoln Burrows.

120
00:06:32.325 --> 00:06:34.626
He's being executed
in three weeks.

121
00:06:34.694 --> 00:06:37.028
Well. I'm aware of
that. What's that to you?

122
00:06:37.731 --> 00:06:39.014
He's my brother.

123
00:06:41.318 --> 00:06:43.329
When I knew I was
being sent to prison.

124
00:06:43.353 --> 00:06:45.820
my attorney petitioned the DOC.

125
00:06:45.889 --> 00:06:47.271
So you could be near him.

126
00:06:47.340 --> 00:06:48.640
That's right.

127
00:06:51.478 --> 00:06:53.111
Don't take that away from me.

128
00:06:54.714 --> 00:06:55.997
Not until it's over.

129
00:06:57.734 --> 00:07:00.535
I'm not the one
behind the transfer.

130
00:07:00.604 --> 00:07:02.787
You're up against much
bigger fish than me.

131
00:07:05.976 --> 00:07:07.808
I'll arrange for you
to say goodbye.

132
00:07:08.945 --> 00:07:10.545
You ship out tomorrow.

133
00:08:37.433 --> 00:08:38.978
I'm going into
the walls tonight.

134
00:08:39.002 --> 00:08:40.418
See if I can access the roof.

135
00:08:40.487 --> 00:08:42.807
You gonna tell me
about the transfer?

136
00:08:43.173 --> 00:08:44.639
I'm taking care of it.

137
00:08:44.707 --> 00:08:46.774
You're taking care of it?

138
00:08:46.843 --> 00:08:48.643
Sounds to me like
you're reaching.

139
00:08:49.246 --> 00:08:50.678
Maybe.

140
00:08:50.747 --> 00:08:51.947
A little.

141
00:08:51.982 --> 00:08:54.599
A little.

142
00:08:54.668 --> 00:08:56.846
You know. I'd made my
peace with what was coming.

143
00:08:56.870 --> 00:08:58.470
Then you show up

144
00:08:58.538 --> 00:09:01.206
and give me the one thing a
man in my situation shouldn't have.

145
00:09:01.274 --> 00:09:03.874
Hope. And now that's
gonna be taken away.

146
00:09:03.943 --> 00:09:06.444
Don't do this. Linc.
I got three weeks.

147
00:09:06.513 --> 00:09:07.996
What do you want me to do?

148
00:09:08.465 --> 00:09:09.597
Hmm?

149
00:09:14.454 --> 00:09:15.774
Come on. Michael.

150
00:09:15.822 --> 00:09:17.422
What do you want me to do?

151
00:09:19.493 --> 00:09:21.209
Bring her back.

152
00:09:21.277 --> 00:09:23.478
You know I can't do that.

153
00:09:23.546 --> 00:09:27.365
But. look. there's
some stuff that I can do.

154
00:09:27.434 --> 00:09:30.718
It's not gonna be the same.
but we're gonna figure it out.

155
00:09:30.786 --> 00:09:32.170
And no matter what.

156
00:09:32.238 --> 00:09:33.855
it's still gonna be me and you.

157
00:09:35.859 --> 00:09:38.626
Okay. But what if
something happens to you?

158
00:09:40.397 --> 00:09:42.997
You just have a little faith.

159
00:09:51.024 --> 00:09:52.524
Just have a little faith.

160
00:09:57.096 --> 00:09:58.456
All right. here's the deal.

161
00:09:58.481 --> 00:10:00.281
If we believe Lincoln.
this tape is a lie.

162
00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:01.449
It has to be.

163
00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:03.095
But you saw it. It's all there.

164
00:10:03.119 --> 00:10:06.119
Yeah. but maybe what we're
looking for is what's not there.

165
00:10:07.557 --> 00:10:09.774
Okay. Steadman.

166
00:10:09.843 --> 00:10:11.676
You see? What's he looking at?

167
00:10:11.745 --> 00:10:13.127
A car. a pedestrian.

168
00:10:13.196 --> 00:10:14.962
No. no. His eye
line is too high. right?

169
00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:16.809
It's like he's looking
right into the camera.

170
00:10:16.833 --> 00:10:18.350
He might as well
be saying "cheese."

171
00:10:20.687 --> 00:10:22.120
Now he just sits there.

172
00:10:22.188 --> 00:10:24.500
Like 10. 15 seconds.
as if he was maybe...

173
00:10:24.524 --> 00:10:26.357
Waiting for someone. Right.

174
00:10:28.195 --> 00:10:29.677
There. That's a 9 mm.

175
00:10:29.746 --> 00:10:31.812
Shouldn't there be some
kind of kick or something?

176
00:10:31.881 --> 00:10:33.081
Lincoln's pretty strong.

177
00:10:33.166 --> 00:10:35.133
Yeah. but strong
enough to bury a recoil?

178
00:10:35.902 --> 00:10:38.052
Now. you shoot someone.

179
00:10:38.121 --> 00:10:39.571
supposedly for revenge.

180
00:10:39.639 --> 00:10:40.855
do you take the time

181
00:10:40.924 --> 00:10:42.301
to go back in and
hit the glove box.

182
00:10:42.325 --> 00:10:43.903
or do you just get
the hell out of there?

183
00:10:43.927 --> 00:10:46.289
Feds said he was trying to
make it look like a robbery.

184
00:10:46.313 --> 00:10:47.411
No.

185
00:10:48.831 --> 00:10:50.048
Look.

186
00:10:50.100 --> 00:10:52.700
Look at Lincoln's angle
as he leaves the frame.

187
00:10:52.769 --> 00:10:54.168
Mmm.

188
00:10:54.237 --> 00:10:55.703
Walks away from the car.

189
00:10:56.973 --> 00:10:58.439
Now this guy.

190
00:10:58.508 --> 00:11:00.925
who conveniently hides
his face from the camera.

191
00:11:00.994 --> 00:11:02.660
he comes back in. Why?

192
00:11:02.729 --> 00:11:05.691
To explain the bloody pants they'd
already planted in his apartment.

193
00:11:05.715 --> 00:11:07.515
Nick. this is great. Yeah.

194
00:11:08.718 --> 00:11:09.896
Who should we go to?

195
00:11:09.920 --> 00:11:10.985
Nobody. Yet.

196
00:11:11.054 --> 00:11:12.654
I mean. to the
unbiased eye. we're just

197
00:11:12.722 --> 00:11:14.289
backing a horse
that died in the gate.

198
00:11:14.357 --> 00:11:15.840
A lot of what-ifs
and conjecture.

199
00:11:15.909 --> 00:11:18.743
You know. we don't have
anything. We need some evidence.

200
00:11:18.812 --> 00:11:21.195
Look. if... if Lincoln
didn't fire this gun.

201
00:11:21.264 --> 00:11:23.964
then somebody with some serious
skills went to work on this tape

202
00:11:24.033 --> 00:11:27.153
to prove that he did. Fine.
But how do we prove that?

203
00:11:28.338 --> 00:11:30.054
I know a guy.

204
00:11:30.123 --> 00:11:31.839
You know a guy?

205
00:11:31.908 --> 00:11:33.408
Yeah. I know a guy.

206
00:11:34.344 --> 00:11:35.610
Thanks.

207
00:11:36.713 --> 00:11:38.875
Seems we need to
have another powwow.

208
00:11:38.899 --> 00:11:40.948
There's been talk about
you packing your bags.

209
00:11:41.017 --> 00:11:42.750
Don't believe
everything you hear.

210
00:11:42.819 --> 00:11:44.151
I'm not going anywhere.

211
00:11:48.124 --> 00:11:51.259
You know. I have a really
hard time trusting you. Fish.

212
00:11:51.328 --> 00:11:54.428
The important thing is
that we stay on schedule.

213
00:11:54.497 --> 00:11:56.181
Yeah? English. Fitz or Percy?

214
00:11:56.249 --> 00:11:57.731
English. Fitz or Percy.

215
00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:00.279
You wanna know which one
I think we should take out?

216
00:12:00.303 --> 00:12:02.269
All due respect. I
don't need opinions.

217
00:12:02.905 --> 00:12:04.422
I need answers.

218
00:12:04.491 --> 00:12:06.185
Remember. the warden
leaves at 5:00 tonight.

219
00:12:06.209 --> 00:12:08.375
So by 5:05. we're
gonna need that key.

220
00:12:08.461 --> 00:12:11.479
And how is this key gonna
give you the answers?

221
00:12:11.548 --> 00:12:13.131
I'll worry about that.

222
00:12:13.199 --> 00:12:14.810
You worry about getting the key.

223
00:12:14.834 --> 00:12:17.068
Hey. this key

224
00:12:17.137 --> 00:12:18.703
better be worth it.

225
00:12:18.772 --> 00:12:19.954
Understand?

226
00:12:26.813 --> 00:12:29.848
Afternoon. Mr. Scofield.

227
00:12:29.916 --> 00:12:32.951
I need to know if there's any
way to block a transfer order.

228
00:12:33.019 --> 00:12:34.419
There's about 50 ways.

229
00:12:34.487 --> 00:12:36.420
All right. I'll take
the quickest.

230
00:12:37.139 --> 00:12:38.506
You file a motion

231
00:12:38.575 --> 00:12:41.409
for what they call an
interlocutory injunction.

232
00:12:41.478 --> 00:12:42.610
How long does that take?

233
00:12:42.679 --> 00:12:44.278
How fast can you write?

234
00:12:44.347 --> 00:12:48.500
A man can claim almost anything
violates his constitutional rights.

235
00:12:48.568 --> 00:12:50.513
There's. uh.
environmental issues.

236
00:12:50.537 --> 00:12:52.417
allergies. religious
requirements.

237
00:12:52.471 --> 00:12:54.200
Take your pick. What
if they don't buy it?

238
00:12:54.224 --> 00:12:57.019
Don't matter. Court's required
by law to hear your motion.

239
00:12:57.043 --> 00:12:59.394
Till they do. you
can't be transferred.

240
00:12:59.462 --> 00:13:00.923
Hell. they've been
trying to move

241
00:13:00.947 --> 00:13:03.898
my tired gray
behind for 10 years.

242
00:13:03.966 --> 00:13:06.517
God bless the
American legal system.

243
00:13:07.721 --> 00:13:10.438
Why do you want to
stay in here so badly?

244
00:13:10.507 --> 00:13:13.357
There's someone here I
can't bear to leave behind.

245
00:13:14.593 --> 00:13:17.428
I guess that means we
got something in common.

246
00:13:18.981 --> 00:13:21.543
The State's requiring a
physical for Lincoln Burrows.

247
00:13:21.567 --> 00:13:23.379
You heard the news.
didn't you? Thanks.

248
00:13:23.403 --> 00:13:24.469
No. what?

249
00:13:24.537 --> 00:13:25.714
They're brothers.

250
00:13:25.738 --> 00:13:27.571
Who? Burrows and Scofield.

251
00:13:28.725 --> 00:13:30.174
Michael Scofield?

252
00:13:30.243 --> 00:13:32.527
Heard it from one of the
CO's over in Gen Pop.

253
00:13:32.595 --> 00:13:34.106
He didn't say anything
to you about it?

254
00:13:34.130 --> 00:13:35.630
No.

255
00:13:35.698 --> 00:13:38.377
Well. it must be hard to be
here so close to your brother

256
00:13:38.401 --> 00:13:40.601
